liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Port Adelaide lost Dylan Williams to injury and have opted to leave Jeremy Finlayson out of the 22, which is somewhat of a surprise. liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Some sad news this afternoon with word that Ron Barassi, a true legend of our game in every sense, has died at the age of 87. Barassi's family confirmed Ron died today "due to complications from a fall". You can get the full story below. Barassi was a star during the Melbourne Football Club's glory years, helping them to six premierships between 1957 and 1963. A tall, fearless player, he pioneered the position of ruck rover. In 1964, Barassi moved to the Carlton Football Club and won two premierships. From Carlton he went to North Melbourne and won another two premierships with his tough coaching style.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Vale Ron Barassi

featuredLink.title: Ron Barassi, AFL legend and premiership player and coach, dies aged 87

children.content: Some sad news this afternoon with word that Ron Barassi, a true legend of our game in every sense, has died at the age of 87.
Barassi's family confirmed Ron died today "due to complications from a fall".
You can get the full story below.
Barassi was a star during the Melbourne Football Club's glory years, helping them to six premierships between 1957 and 1963.
A tall, fearless player, he pioneered the position of ruck rover.
In 1964, Barassi moved to the Carlton Football Club and won two premierships.
From Carlton he went to North Melbourne and won another two premierships with his tough coaching style.
